    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function's business logic involves calculating the remainder when the input value is divided by 36. This operation is useful in scenarios where a cyclical pattern repeats every 36 units, such as a 36-month period or a 36-item cycle. The workflow is as follows:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "orderedList",
      "content": [
