      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can impact performance when used in large queries or applied to many rows, as they are executed row-by-row. However, given the simplicity of the modulus operation, the performance impact is minimal. It is important to ensure that the function is not used excessively in large datasets or complex queries to avoid potential performance bottlenecks."
